Cubilin

Intermolecular
Cysteine 81 and cysteine 81
Intramolecular
Cysteine 932 and cysteine 958
Cysteine 1218 and cysteine 1240
Cysteine 1333 and cysteine 1351
Cysteine 985 and cysteine 1005
Cysteine 1165 and cysteine 1191
Cysteine 1278 and cysteine 1306
Cysteine 1048 and cysteine 1074

6gje B 81 C 81

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between two units of Cubilin at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
